                                                        Wireshark
1.What is Wireshark?
Wireshark is a software tool used to monitor the network traffic through a network interface.
Packet Monitor:There are color codes for each type of packet. The packets are shown with the following information : 
1. Source address 
2. Destination address 
3. Packet type 
4. Hex dump of the packet 
5. Contents of the packet in text 
6. Source port(if applicable) 
7. Destination port(if applicable)

Wireshark can color packets based on rules that match particular fields in packets, to help the user identify the types of traffic.
